metadata.name: fx_dungeon #15
metadata.description:
Welcome to the fx_dungeon. Every cartridge comes loaded with a random amount of levels between 2 (common) and 7 (rare). Your goal is to collect all the coins that are disseminated around the level. Each cartridge comes with the total amount of coins that can be collected displayed on the front. 

Token levels are generated from the transaction hash and are never the same between different tokens. Scattered around the levels are also some random amount of decorative props. There are different types of props, and I added those to the features as well.

Finally, each cartridge comes in different conditions. You could get one in perfect conditions, or one that's been used over and over. Don't worry, each cartridge has been tested and it's working properly anyways!!

This is just a simple game I made learning how to code for creative projects. It's also rumored that's a Golden Edition of this cartridge can be obtained somehow..

## Controls
- Move the player around using WASD or the arrow keys. Interact with stairs using SPACEBAR or E
- You can click the image to toggle sound on or off

## Credits
- I'm using p5js and I also tweaked to my needs a tutorial from Daniel Schiffman about raycasting
- The ambient music is from Joshua McLean, it's called Mountain Trials (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L_OYo2RS8iU&list=PLwJjxqYuirCLkq42mGw4XKGQlpZSfxsYd&index=8) and it's released under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license

metadata.name: Mur #54
metadata.description:
Mur is a series of computational drawings of stacked and falling bricks. The bricks are placed in different configurations of walls, towers, stacks and paths, and are then exposed to gravity. 

The graphics are coded with p5.js and the rigid body simulations with ammo.js. In live mode, press 's' to save a screenshot and 'e' to save a high resolution image. Press 't' to toggle textures. 

Each scene is drawn twice, first brick by brick as they fall or stay in place, then the scene as a whole. Mur is optimized for Chrome, uses WebGL and may not work in all browsers.

metadata.name: Fx(poritz) #2
metadata.description:
Fx(poritz) is a generative NFT collection of mysterious and magical creatures. This is a continuation of my previous work published on Hic et Nunc/Teia.

It was build with layered PNGs, using Photoshop and the Paint3D software. There are 5 features, and every iteration generates an unique poritz to call yours. There is 5% of chance to generate a RGB poritz, and 3% to mint a Trippy one.

I’d like to thank Ciphrd for the permission to use the ‘RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton’ reference in this project, Everik Titanker for the help with the 3D basis model, and PureSpider for the Github template of the code used here. Much much love <3.

metadata.name: Outside your Window #82
metadata.description:
Never take for granted that we sit in the safety of our homes, behind our windows, sheltered from the elements outside. 

The characteristics of the rain outside the window, and the window itself, will be determined by the mint hash. However, the background color of this piece will constantly change based on the hour of day it is loaded, hence note that the thumbnail will only technically be accurate 1/24 hours out of the day as it represents a static snapshot taken at the time of token rendering.

100% of the primary proceeds will be donated towards flood relief efforts for the devastating December 2021 floods in Malaysia.

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Phantoms #254
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Rings #1
metadata.description:
Rings is the cummulative texturized generative artwork obtained after several animations of a determinated number of particles seeking a concentric pattern in several rings. But in this case, to get some different results of depth and texture, the chosen particles weregeometrical 2D shapes (like lines, circles, squares and triangles). Also, white 1D dots with low stroke in a descentralized radius from pattern center brings a nice highlighting effect, helping the depth feeling.
All the codes were developed and studyed for a quite time, and after a high number of tests and modifications I believe Rings is ready to be yours!

Its a big pleasure be back :)

And again....palletes carefully chosen.

See the features! Ranking system set up!

Press 's' to save canvas.
Nice experience at full view.

metadata.name: Reconnaissance #349
metadata.description:
An immense quiet accompanies a sense of looming futility while peering down across vast new worlds. What use is there in discovering and documenting these unknown places? Who would care to seek out lifeless lands lost in the cosmos?

Any civilization capable of such reconnaissance might seem above the little hope that barren lands may bring. Unless, of course, there is a hope of answering the most desperate of needs: Finding a New Home.

Were these images captured by humans on Earth, or on Mars, or somewhere even further away in distance and probability? Maybe they’re recon from another planet’s civilization — one that shares our struggle to find true harmony with the world they have.

Inspired by the remarkable satellite imagery in the compendium “This is Mars,” Reconnaissance suggests what may lie outside our habitable lands — and that we risk missing what's already here while being compelled to look further and further for what’s next.


Choose a resolution (1-6) by adding "&scale=4" to the URL in live view.
Created with p5.js

TENDER x Nat Sarkissian
May 2022
